description:
We begin in the valley in Kaga slowly grinding our way through the mountains, up highway route 364 using the shoulder for protection. After glimpsing a view of Daishoji reservoir and the Kutani Dam, we avoid the tunnels by snaking our way around up the old roads at the cost of extra climbing. Once reaching the peak of our climb, we are rewarded with views overlooking the Fukui plains. We then begin a sharp descent into said valley, briefly passing through the small village of Maruokach≈ç-yamatakeda on our way down. 

We exit the mountains and enter onto the plains at the town of Maruoka, where we visit Maruoka Castle - one of only twelve original castles still standing. We then travel south on route 8 until we reach the city of Fukui for lunch. We will also drop in at Fukui Station to investigate the animatronic dinosaurs hanging around outside. We then continue travelling south on route 229 until Shimmei, where we fork off to instead zigzag through the residential houses before eventually connecting with the Hino River which we will then follow to our final destination - the city of Echizen.
